quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
50,16,"Surely We {1} have created man, and We know the promptings of his heart, and We are nearer to him than even his jugular vein. {2}",footnotes:1:After presenting the arguments for the Hereafter
50,17,"Moreover, there are two scribes, one each sitting on the right and the left, recording everything."
50,18,"He utters not a word, but there is a vigilant watcher at hand. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
50,19,"Lo, the agony of death has indeed come with the Truth. {1} That is what you had sought to avoid. {2}",footnotes:1:“Come with the truth” implies that the agony of death is the starting point when the reality which had remained concealed in the world
50,20,"And then the Trumpet was blown. {1} This is the day of the promised chastisement.",footnotes:1:This implies that blowing of the Trumpet at which all dead men will rise back to life in their own physical bodies. For explanation
50,21,"Everyone has come, each attended by one who will drive him on, and another who will bear witness. {1}",footnotes:1:Most probably this implies the same two angels who had been appointed for compiling the record of the words and deeds of the person in the world. On the Day of Resurrection
50,22,"You were heedless of this. Now We have removed your veil and so your vision today is sharp. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
50,23,"His companion said:“ Here is he who was in my charge.” {1}",footnotes:1:Some commentators say that the companion implies the angel who has been referred to as a witness in( verse 21). He will say: I have this person’s record ready with me here. Some other commentators say that the companion implies the satan who was attached to the person in the world. He will say: This person whom I was controlling and preparing for Hell
50,24,"The command was given: “Cast into Hell {1} every hardened, stubborn unbeliever, {2}",footnotes:1:As the context shows this command will be given to the two angels who had taken the culprit into their custody as soon as he had risen from the grave
50,25,"who hinders good, {1} exceeds the limits, {2} is immersed in doubts, {3}",footnotes:1:Khair in Arabic is used both for wealth and for goodness. According to the first meaning
50,26,"and has set up another deity with Allah. Hurl him into the grievous torment.” {1}",footnotes:1:Allah
50,27,"His companion said:“ I did not incite him to rebel; he was far gone into error of his own accord.” {1}",footnotes:1:Here by companion is meant the satan who was attached to the disobedient person in the world. And this also becomes evident from the style that both the person and his satan are disputing between themselves in the court of Allah. He says: My Lord
50,28,"(It was said): “Do not remonstrate in My presence. I had warned you. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
50,29,"My Word is not changed; {1} and never do I inflict the least wrong upon My servants.” {2}",footnotes:1:That is
50,30,"On that Day We shall ask Hell: “Are you full?” And it will reply: “Are there any more?” {1}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings:
50,31,"And when Paradise shall be brought close to the God-fearing, and will no longer be far away, {1}",footnotes:1:That is
50,32,"it will be said: “This is what you were promised, a promise made to everyone who turned much (to Allah) {1} and was watchful of his conduct, {2}",footnotes:1:The word awwab is very extensive in meaning. It implies the person who might have adopted the way of obedience and Allah’s goodwill instead of the way of disobedience
50,33,"to everyone who feared the Merciful One though He is beyond the reach of perception, {1} to everyone who has come with a heart ever wont to turn (to Him). {2}",footnotes:1:The word munib in the original is derived from inabat
50,34,"Enter this Paradise in peace.” {1} That will be the Day of Eternity.",footnotes:1:If the word salam in udkhuluha bi-salamin is taken in the meaning of peace and security
50,35,"Therein they shall get whatever they desire; and with Us there is even more. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
